{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c6416a29-da56-429e-9300-4e5f3d000007","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default**. You no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`. You can simply remove that property:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01XpFfnZdRnxjjT3oFZudByM","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01YSUejcKRmvgymgJXTCq42L","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-97908d1ee9034d4fb62bfb655fee198d/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":"\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-97908d1ee9034d4fb62bfb655fee198d/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"aab88e24-f86e-4964-a695-9028fad8e080","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) via `EnableMSTestRunner`. They have `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to `true`.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as the default test runner. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property was needed in .NET 9 to opt-in to MTP support with `dotnet test`, but in .NET 10 it's no longer needed — MTP is the default.\n\n\nSince .NET 10 has native MTP support built into `dotnet test`, they can safely remove that property from their project file.","outputTokens":437},"id":"823c753e-f382-4d02-bb49-cd2a54c6e1bd","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:23:06.129Z","parentId":"f243b5e5-24fa-4ecf-bccd-0c589c9449ae"}
