{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3b8d620f-eadd-4c85-a539-2c8c83bada16","content":"Here's the summary:\n\n**No, you don't need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` anymore.** That property was the .NET 9 opt-in to route `dotnet test` through MTP. In .NET 10, MTP is the **default** test coordination protocol for `dotnet test`, so the property is unnecessary.\n\nYour remaining setup is all you need:\n\n- **`EnableMSTestRunner`** — builds your test project as an MTP executable\n- **`OutputType: Exe`** — required for the above\n- **`MSTest` 3.8.0** — includes the MTP hosting\n\nJust run `dotnet test` as usual and it will use MTP natively.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aab88e24-f86e-4964-a695-9028fad8e080","outputTokens":168},"id":"cacaa661-1a4c-4899-8978-d915c70a05fb","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:23:22.687Z","parentId":"5e9101a2-b73b-44e4-8b82-2fd908034863"}
